For flags with a short form, a
.Fl -no-X
alias is also accepted (e.g.
.Fl -no-h
for
.Fl -no-header ,
.Fl -no-Z
for
.Fl -no-total ,
.Fl -no-C
for
.Fl -no-count ,
.Fl -no-g
for
.Fl -no-group ,
.Fl -no-i
for
.Fl -no-inode ,
.Fl -no-H
for
.Fl -no-links ,
.Fl -no-S
for
.Fl -no-blocks ,
.Fl -no-o
for
.Fl -no-octal ,
.Fl -no-u
for
.Fl -no-user ,
.Fl -no-z
for
.Fl -no-size ,
.Fl -no-M
for
