.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl M , Fl -permissions , Fl -no-permissions
Show or suppress the permissions field.
.Fl -mode
/
.Fl -no-mode
are accepted as long aliases (matching traditional Unix terminology).
.Fl -no-M
is a hidden short-letter alias for
.Fl -no-permissions .
.It Fl z , Fl -size , Fl -no-size
Show or suppress the file size field.
.Fl -filesize
/
.Fl -no-filesize
are accepted as hidden aliases.
.Fl -no-z
is a hidden short-letter alias for
.Fl -no-size .
.It Fl u , Fl -user , Fl -no-user
Show or suppress the user field.
.Fl -no-u
is a hidden short-letter alias for
.Fl -no-user .
.It Fl -uid , Fl -no-uid
Show or suppress the numeric user ID column (long-form only).
.It Fl -gid , Fl -no-gid
Show or suppress the numeric group ID column (long-form only).
.It Fl -no-time
Clear all timestamp columns from the base format.
Runs
.Em before
individual timestamp adds, so
.Sy --no-time --accessed
leaves just the accessed column.
Accepts
.Fl -no-timestamps
as a hidden alias.
.It Fl -no-modified , Fl -no-changed , Fl -no-accessed , Fl -no-created
Suppress individual timestamp columns.
.Fl -no-m
and
.Fl -no-c
are accepted as hidden short-letter aliases for
.Fl -no-modified
and
.Fl -no-changed
respectively.
Unlike
.Fl -no-time ,
these run
.Em after
individual adds, so they beat an explicit
.Fl -modified
on the same command line.
.It Fl -no-inode
Suppress the inode field.
.It Fl -no-group
Suppress the group field.
.It Fl -no-links
Suppress the hard links field.
.It Fl -no-blocks
Suppress the blocks field.
.It Fl -no-octal
Suppress the octal permissions column.
.It Fl -no-header
Suppress the header row.
